  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the effect of pectin, a kind of soluble dietary
      fiber, on colonic transit time, clinical symptoms and the gut microbiota in adults with
      slow-transit constipation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients were randomized to receive either pectin or placebo. Treatment consisted of 4 weeks
      supplementation with pectin (fiber group) or placebo. We evaluated the colonic transit time,
      constipation symptoms and fecal bacterial population in two groups.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
